headline: Dive Deposits: Wells Fargo looks inward on real-estate right-sizing
summary: The bank appears to be consolidating its office footprint in its home city. It isn’t the only lender reevaluating real estate: JPMorgan is expanding in Orlando, and Valley National is selling $925 million in loans.

headline: Wells Fargo price target raised to $79 from $61 at Keefe Bruyette
summary: Keefe Bruyette raised the firm’s price target on Wells Fargo (WFC) to $79 from $61 and keeps a Market Perform rating on the shares. The U.S. bank stocks have had a strong run following better than expected earnings and, more importantly, the election results, the analyst tells investors in a research note.
